<body>

   
    <div class="recipe-container">
        <h1>Soft & Fluffy Uttapam Recipe</h1>
       

        <h2>Ingredients:</h2>
        <ul class="ingredients-list">
            <li>2 cups Dosa Batter</li>
            <li>1/2 cup Finely Chopped Onions</li>
            <li>1/2 cup Chopped Tomatoes</li>
            <li>1/4 cup Chopped Capsicum</li>
            <li>2 Green Chilies (finely chopped)</li>
            <li>2 tbsp Coriander Leaves (chopped)</li>
            <li>Oil for Cooking</li>
            <li>Salt to taste</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Instructions:</h2>
        <ol class="instructions-list">
            <li>Heat a tawa and grease it lightly with oil.</li>
            <li>Pour a ladle of dosa batter and spread it slightly thick.</li>
            <li>Sprinkle chopped onions, tomatoes, capsicum, green chilies, and coriander on top.</li>
            <li>Drizzle some oil around the uttapam and cook on medium flame.</li>
            <li>Flip carefully and cook until both sides are golden brown.</li>
            <li>Serve hot with coconut chutney and sambar.</li>
        </ol>
    </div>

</body>
